short_description: A madcap romp through the 1980's NYC art scene amid the colorful career of painter, Edward Brezinski, hell-bent on making it. Filmed in NYC, Detroit, San Francisco, Ireland, Berlin and the Cote d'Azur.

The supernova exploded leaving in its wake...a frustrating 'Duchampian light' era of art (like a peace of dust called 'dust' that often leaves museum goers empty but seems to never give way to the PAINTERS. Can this be rectified?"), ('https://m.media-amazon.com/images/M/MV5BNDYxODc4NTU0OF5BMl5BanBnXkFtZTgwODM2MTYyNzE@._V1_.jpg', "Marguerite Van Cook and James Romberger, artists of extraordinary ability, discuss their close friendship with Edward Brezinski of whom they showed at their famous Ground Zero Gallery in the 80's NYC. When Brezinski died suddenly in a hotel in Nice in 2007, he had Marguerite's phone number on his person so she was called by the authorities in France on New Years Day, 2007 to inform her as such. Of note - Sid Vicious called Marguerite with his phone call from jail after he stabbed Nancy. short_description: A couple of military police, two women and a 13-year-old teenager are found dead at home. One of the most controversial crimes in Brazil, with two episodes bringing different visions of what actually happened.
